## 4. Side-by-Side Comparison: Germany vs. Austria Student Visa

To help you and your parents make a clear decision, here is a simple side-by-side comparison of Germany and Austria under the 2026 guidelines:

| Feature | Study in Germany | Study in Austria (Zero Blocked Account) |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Public University Tuition** | Free (Only Semester fee of €150 to €350) | Free (Only Semester fee of **€726**) |
| **Blocked Account Required** | **Yes (Mandatory)** | **No (Not Required)** |
| **Funds Frozen Abroad** | **€11,904 (~₹11.5 Lakhs)** frozen in Germany | **Zero Rupees** frozen in Europe |
| **Funds Location** | German Bank (Sperrkonto) | **Your Savings Bank Account in India** |
| **Age-based monthly limits** | Standard €992/month for everyone | Under 24: **€722.58/month**<br>24 or older: **€1,308.39/month** |
| **Rent Offset Rule** | None (You pay rent out of your monthly payouts) | If rent is > **€386.43/month**, show the difference in India |
| **Emergency Fund Access** | Impossible (Locked in Germany) | **100% accessible** at any time in India |
| **Official Authorities** | [Auswärtiges Amt](https://www.auswaertiges-amt.de/en) & [DAAD](https://www.daad.de/en/) | [OeAD](https://oead.at/en/) & [BMEIA](https://www.bmeia.gv.at/en/) |

