## 5. Why Local Consultants Hide Austria and the Finesse Transparency Guarantee

If Austria is such a fantastic option, why haven't you heard about it from the other study abroad consultancies in Pune, Kolhapur, or Sangli?

The answer is simple: **Agent Commissions.**

### The Agency Business Model Exposed
Most commercial education agents in India operate on a commission model. They partner with private universities or lower-tier colleges in the UK, USA, Canada, and Australia. Every time they enroll a student, these private colleges pay them a **10% to 15% commission** (which is usually ₹1.5 Lakhs to ₹3 Lakhs per student). 

*   **Austrian Government Universities:** Austrian government universities are public institutions. They do not charge high tuition fees, and they **never pay commission to any agent**. 
*   **The Result:** Since agents cannot make money from Austrian university admissions, they hide this country from you. Instead, they will push you towards expensive private universities in other countries where they get paid a fat commission, even if it means your family has to take huge loans.

